Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION recognizing the Alaska
2 Christian Church on their 190th anniversary.
3 Whereas, Nestled in the hills of Morgan and Owen counties
4 is the quiet unincorporated town of Alaska, Indiana, where
5 early Hoosier settlers sought to establish a place of worship;
6 Whereas, In the early nineteenth century, the Alaska
7 Christian Church was established as a friendly Christian
8 community, welcoming all to worship and serve; and
9 Whereas, A testament to the lasting impact it has made on
10 the community, the Alaska Christian Church has now been a
11 foundation of Morgan and Owen counties for 190 years:
12 Therefore,
13 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
14 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
15 SECTION 1. That the Indiana Senate congratulates the
16 Alaska Christian Church on the occasion of their 190th
17 anniversary.
2026 RR 3534/DI JR

2
1 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby directed
2 to transmit copies of this Resolution to the Alaska Christian
3 Church.
2026 RR 3534/DI JR

